From the time completion/error rate results and observation findings, we made some improvements to our prototype: 1. Making the taxi booking button and corresponding page more intuitive 2. Based on user feedback on navigation and flow, we made some chan
text.tspan: 1. Making the taxi booking button and corresponding page more intuitive
2. Based on user feedback on navigation and flow, we made some changes such as removing the
‘document’ tab and moving the document function within the ‘profile’ tab; moving the ‘home’ button
from top left to the bottom bar.
3. Based on other feedback we got, we have changed the calendar view and added buttons for
switching between different months; we have added ‘cancel’, ‘done’ button and task completion tick
The testing also showed that users started to notice some navigation and flow issues, which
provided us with valuable feedback. This has again confirmed the importance of involving users
As we recruited some of the users from our previous paper testing for the digital testing, we also
found that compared to other users, these users were more willing to contribute and suggest
improvements for our prototype, which suggests that they had more ‘product ownership’ than
